			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">This forum has too much political debate in it.  Time to switch to something more pertinent.  I'm hoping that some others who might not normally post will come in and share their opinions.  I just got done reading this interview: <a href="http://www.gamemethod.com/archive/214.php" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.gamemethod.com/archive/214.php</a> and this talking point: <a href="http://www.wtfman.com/oldnews/oct03.htm" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.wtfman.com/oldnews/oct03.htm</a> (look under "Carebears in games")
<br />

<br />
So here's my point of discussion...PVP.  Are most of today's modern games too shielded from PVP?  
<br />

<br />
When I first started reading the article my thought was no.  I'm happy to not be ripped off and have to be looking over my shoulder.  But then I started thinking about my DaoC days.  I remember running around the frontier (at level 30) and getting ambushed by a crowd of PvP'ers.  I remember being frustrated.  But more importantly I remember the even quite clearly.  One time out there I had a SoB invis guy much higher than me camping my corpse.  Funny thing was I also remember what happened next.  I remember saying something to my (then) guildmates and about 6 of them coming out to find the guy and soundly kicking his ass into the middle of the next MMORPG.  
<br />

<br />
At the time I was really pissed off now but in retrospect I look back and remember how much of a thrill it was to hunt out there.  I was always looking over my shoulder.  Folks were constantly telling me "You're too young to hunt here." (which those that know me is a sure way to get me to make sure I spend the maximum amount of time in said place)  I think that most open PvP games simply lack a type of system that rewards those that play opposing sides while punishing those that just play to grief others.  I think there have been some interesting attempts at such things. (SWG's flag system is IMO an interesting take on it).  Maybe a bounty system or a PK faction system would also be good.  So I'm throwing this out: What do you guys think?<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
