				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">I agree.  That's kind of what I was getting at towards the end of my post.  And, while ambiguous much of the time, so was the fellow I linked to.  Their big beef seems to be that PvP has become cleansed to the point of obscurity and that while griefing is a possibility, it also adds an element of thrill to a game.  I tend to agree with the essence of it.  But at the same time I've played EQ for 3-4 years now and I know griefing is possible even in strict environments so I hold no delusions about what an open PvP system would be like.  I think that a bounty system of some sort would encourage some lawful folks into the hunting of PK'ing griefers and would maybe encourage a whole sub-game to a MM'er.  It could glean a whole "non" class within the game.<span class="gensmall"></span>


