			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Players do want PvP, even if they don't realize it. PvP taps into human vs human battle, which is a limitless source of self-creating content. In any MMORPG, you want that and you want as much of it as you can get.
<br />

<br />
I think, however, that folks may be going about this the wrong way. When you think of PvP, you're thinking of player characters fighting with other player characters. For mandatory PvP that isn't what a lot of people want. I think you'd have far better luck if you let players spawn and play the monsters.
<br />

<br />
You wouldn't have individual monsters as characters that can level up, instead you'd have to have some kind of a ranking system that monster-players could advance on that is separate from the critters they play. Advancement on this scale brings them the ability to play more powerful monsters, opens up more spawn locations around the world for them to play in, and gives them more command abilities such as letting them gather up groups of nearby computer controlled monsters to command as a unit. And that's just the tip of the iceberg.
<br />

<br />
With this kind of a system, you'd end up with a lot of dynamic content, and the PvP aspect is merged completely with the PvE.<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
