			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">EvilNiht have some points there!
<br />

<br />
Basically, it is a lot of work for the staff that design a game.
<br />

<br />
They need to design a game where the PvE system is never maxed and where you can always group more and find it interesting(all while achieving something you feel significant).
<br />

<br />
The day where you NEED to PvP or raid is the day the game is old and need more input bad! (I have nothing against them as long as you never need to do them in order to advance...I will even add that you need to be the best at what you are doing unless someone is better then you actually doing it(groups to groupers, solo to soloers, raids to raiders, and not everything to 1 only)).
<br />

<br />
The day I zone in and get killed without understanding what happen or who did it or why is the day I quit to another game.  I would be strongly displeased to leave a zone because someone warn me and may quit over a long period of time* but to been kill just because they are in the zone and are uberers and dont care to talk, it make me leave right away a few times in the past(a few texts MMORPG).
<br />

<br />
As long as PvP(or raids) are something more and that I still can do PvE all the time and find it uberer and uberer and uberer, NP.  The day I have no more grouping or soloing to do, I find it silly to see only an aspect I dont actually enjoy.  It would not be hard to add limitless amount of working to be done on grouping without removing the rest and without making the current stuff obsolete.  For exemple, they could add levels that only apply to some zones...I would jump in them and play there a LOT.  Even if they dont apply in PoP, who care about it, I dont even want to go there again, so...I would happily work on level 90438876589 in the 9847 layers of the abyss even if I am still 65 in PoP and could work on others stuff, there would not even be an hesitation.  Yet, who know, I could maybe consider others stuff, as long as they are not the only option left.
<br />

<br />
Basically, I want to be able to advance more, and more and more.  Sitting on my level 65 and feeling Uber is the worst thing for me.  Even if past a point it dont give anything at all but those selected restricted dungeons, I would be there.  <img src="images/smiles/razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" />   I am sure could find something after, but the whole idea that levels actually help you in raids is presponderous at best, how in hell will it help you against a God to have kill goblins?  The systems should be spread.  And been able to beat a God should not help you much against goblins, I am pretty sure if you can beat a God you can learn to beat goblins, but you have to learn it, it is not the same tactics, not the same approach, nothing in commons...
<br />

<br />
Once they fix that, PvP and any other system could be work...
<br />

<br />
Ano
<br />

<br />
*1* It mostly depend if the game have something else to offer me, since if I cant play it when I want, then I may play something else.<span class="gensmall"></span>


